	  and GGZ_ROOM_LEAVE events better (with a better message).

2004-02-09 09:35   Jason Short <jdorje@ggzgamingzone.org>

	* ggz-gtk/game.h: Remove the (unused) global "game" variable.'

2004-02-09 09:28   Jason Short <jdorje@ggzgamingzone.org>

	* ggz-gtk/game.c: Cleanups and fixes for leaving a game.    -
	  GGZ_GAME_OVER, GGZ_GAME_IO_ERROR, and GGZ_GAME_PROTO_ERROR
	  GGZCore game	    events are removed.  The first is quite
	  worthless and the latter two	    are unused.  GGZCore now
	  handles these events internally.    - When the game client exits,
	  ggzcore frees the game structure.  Later	if a table join
	  succeeds and there's no game structure present, we	  know we
	  don't actually have a game running so we tell ggzd we've left
	  the table.

